    },
    "leadership": "No fixed leader; any proposer may start. Multiple proposers may contend; safety still holds via quorum intersection, while liveness is achieved when contention stabilizes and a successful round completes.",
    "(c) majority/quorum requirement for progress": {
      "quorum_size": "Majority of N acceptors: ⌈N/2⌉ + 1",
      "how_used": "Prepare phase requires a majority of promises; accept phase requires a majority of accepts. The intersection of majorities enforces safety (the same chosen value cannot be contradicted in later rounds)."
    },
    "safety/liveness guarantees (high level)": {
      "safety": "If a value is chosen in some round, any later round that gathers a majority will have to propagate/choose that same value (enforced by the prepare/promise rule and majority intersection).",
      "liveness": "Assuming failures stop and proposers keep retrying, eventually a round can collect the needed majorities and complete choosing a value."
    }
  },
  "raft": {
    "(a) consensus problem": "Agreement on a replicated log (and thus a deterministic state machine): all servers apply the same commands in the same order. Safety: committed entries are never overwritten; state machine safety holds because servers apply entries only after commitment in the replicated log order. Liveness: a live leader can make progress by replicating entries and committing them when a majority acknowledges.",
    "roles": {
