    "leadership": "There is a designated leader per term, elected via majority vote. Log replication and commitment are driven by the leader; when the leader fails, a new election selects a new leader.",
    "(c) majority/quorum requirement for progress": {
      "quorum_size": "Majority of N servers: ⌈N/2⌉ + 1",
      "how_used": "Leader election requires majority votes; committing a log entry requires replication to a majority (the leader advances commitIndex when an entry is present on a majority)."
    },
    "state_machine safety (high level)": "Only entries committed by a leader (i.e., known to be on a majority in that term) are applied by servers; the log/commit rules ensure committed entries persist and all state machines apply the same sequence."
